tif

Class MetadataTIF

  • java.lang.Object
    • tif.MetadataTIF
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseMetadata, Metadata<DirectoryIFD>, java.lang.Iterable<DirectoryIFD>

    public class MetadataTIF
extends java.lang.Object
implements Metadata<DirectoryIFD>
    A composite leaf component of the Composite design pattern that encapsulates Exif metadata stored in TIFF-style directories. This class is typically used to manage and organise metadata extracted from TIFF, JPEG, or PNG (via eXIf chunks) image files.

    It stores a map of DirectoryIFD instances, indexed by their DirectoryIdentifier, providing access, mutation, and query capabilities for structured image metadata.

    Since:
    13 August 2025

    Author:
